  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Armenia: Strengthening the Integrity of Armenia&apos;s Criminal Justice System</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To reinforce the legislative framework underpinning the foundations of specialized anti-corruption bodies in Armenia and to assist the Government of the Republic of Armenia in applying open, competitive and merit-based recruitment and performance appraisal systems and processes at the Specialized Anti-Corruption Court and the Anti-Corruption Committee. 2) To support the formation of a department within the Prosecutor General&apos;s Office on civil asset forfeiture, including through the delivery of training on the investigation of cases involving illicit assets and application of civil asset forfeiture legislation and surrounding procedure.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Specialized Anti-Corruption Court; the National Assembly of the Republic of Armenia; the Ministry of Justice; the Supreme Judicial Council; and the Prosecutor General&apos;s Office.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to support Armenia&apos;s anti-corruption efforts and reforms by establishing and applying integrity-based institutional management standards for specialized anti-corruption bodies.</narrative>
  </description>
